(Import [(57hq ([(Work Vocation) (Work Leadership)] Decision [|Specialized lanes are made explicit via skill files and orchestrate role discipline, and agents may create/adopt new lanes (e.g. nota-designer) when a topic demands it. cluster-operator handles live maintenance and production lojix. cloud-designer/cloud-operator are cloud-scoped lanes with their own report subdirs and orchestrate-cli claim support. system-designer handles system topics (CriomOS, horizon, lojix, goldragon, deployment), renamed from system-assistant; system-specialist is renamed system-operator. videographer is a new main role for video as craft (capture, editing, captioning, encoding, publishing-prep), paralleling poet.|] High Minimum Zero [cluster-operator cloud-designer cloud-operator system-designer system-operator nota-designer videographer])) (7nbu ([(Work Vocation)] Principle [Designer's deliverable is intent / architecture / skills, not reports] High Minimum Zero [designer])) (2gj4 ([(Work Vocation) (Work Leadership)] Decision [|Add an auditor role that closes the loop back to designer — mostly mechanical (doubter that finds flaws, bad patterns, broken workspace rules; knows the rules). Automate it; a smaller rules-and-flaws model (DeepSeek) is the main auditor going forward.|] Medium Minimum Zero [auditor deepseek designer])) (beue ([(Work Vocation)] Clarification [Concept designer is an ephemeral occasional invocation, not a persistent named lane] Medium Minimum Zero [concept-designer])) (x92t ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Management)))] Principle [|Role-token-driven skill loading: each token in a lane's role vector contributes to the default skill bundle the persona-mind sends at boot. A lane with role [PersonaSignal Designer] loads the base designer skills (skills/designer.md) plus persona-signal-specific skills; [Note Designer] loads designer skills plus note-specific. Specialization tokens map directly to skill files (or skill bundles registered for that token). Composes with the existing intent that skills bundle into roles (intent/persona.nota 2026-05-20T17:30); refines it by making the bundle composition derivable from the role vector rather than from a single role string.|] Medium Minimum Zero [persona-mind role-vector skill-loading])) (081i ([(Knowledge Taxonomy)] Decision [Domain-vocabulary hierarchy is structural — tree nesting plus scope-prefix matching, not a directional relation: a domain nested under another IS subsumed by it. Cross-tree domain relations are symmetric equivalence only — synonyms that retrieve together both ways; directional subsumption is dropped because nesting already carries all hierarchy.] VeryHigh VeryHigh Zero [domain-vocabulary spirit])) (4wt3 ([(Knowledge Taxonomy)] Principle [The domain vocabulary is a variable-depth tree where depth is proportional to intent density: dense branches like Software nest a third tier of variants for fine subjects while sparse domains like Hardware stay one or two tiers. Variable depth is the rule, not a structural exception.] VeryHigh VeryHigh Zero [domain-vocabulary])) (2rb7 ([(Knowledge Taxonomy)] Principle [Domain names must be self-explanatory and carry their meaning in the variant name itself. There is no separate gloss or description layer annotating what a domain means; if a name is unclear, rename it rather than annotate it] High High Zero [domain-vocabulary])) (tw15 ([(Knowledge Taxonomy)] Decision [Technology divides into two parallel clusters, Hardware and Software — the true split of technology. Every child of Technology is a cluster with no bare leaves, so all hardware is a queryable scope mirroring the Software cluster.] High High Zero [domain-vocabulary hardware software])) (vfjw ([(Technology (Software Programming))] Clarification [|NOTA strings come exclusively from bracket forms — canonical [text] for ordinary strings and [|text\|] for strings containing brackets (escape-free zone). Brackets ARE the string form; quotation marks do not form string types (the vector-of-characters intuition fits the bracket model). Implementations accepting double-quoted input are non-canonical legacy slated for removal; emitter and parser must behave per this rule.|] VeryHigh High Zero [nota bracket-strings])) (laim ([(Technology (Software Programming))] Decision [NOTA bare string atoms should allow a broad punctuation set. Comments require a double semicolon marker. A single semicolon is ordinary bare atom text. Typed String decoding rejects bracket-delimited strings when the decoded text is eligible for bare atom formatting. *lexical analysis*] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [nota bare-atoms])) (3do3 ([(Technology (Software Programming))] Clarification [all Rust production functions are methods on non-zero-sized data-bearing types or methods on traits, never free functions and never impls on zero-sized placeholder structs used as namespaces; trait methods are preferred but at minimum methods on actual data-bearing struct or enum types are required; tests under cfg-test may have free functions, and fn main is the only other exemption; this isolates four design decisions every Rust author must make - what objects exist, where data lives, where logic lives, what methods belong on what objects; a unit-struct or marker-type impl block is a free function in disguise and forbidden; const-fn and async-fn at module level are also forbidden under this rule; the rule must be carried strongly in the relevant rust skill, revise the skill if stale and rewrite any Rust code that currently violates *programming paradigms*] High High Zero [rust methods data-bearing-types])) (fvtf ([(Technology (Software Programming))] Principle [|NOTA classification is 'qualifies as', not 'is': a token qualifies-as-a-symbol if symbol-safe (PascalCase/camelCase/identifier alphabet); whether it ACTUALLY is a symbol is a type-level question deferred to the macro/schema layer. At parse time promote to the higher classification (qualified-symbol over string) since demoting later under type context is easy while promoting is hard; the schema layer demotes to string-only when its types require.|] High Minimum Zero [nota symbol-classification schema])) (n097 ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces Visualization)))] Constraint [|Visuals in reports are mermaid diagrams (no ASCII text-block diagrams) and belong in reports not chat, where they may be used freely. Keep diagrams short and focused — 4-8 nodes, hard cap ~10; split bigger substance into multiple single-question diagrams (data flow, type lineage, control flow, failure modes) so each reads at a glance. Node labels say what the node IS in 2-5 words; keep bead IDs and file paths out of nodes, in prose or a sibling table. nota/schema design graphs pair each graph with its code surface and ground each scenario in Nix tests.|] High Medium Zero [mermaid reports nota schema])) (b1vi ([(Technology (Software (Systems SystemsProgramming)))] Principle [The text/binary boundary lives in the client: clients translate NOTA text into binary protocol data and render typed replies/traces back to users. Daemons stay free of NOTA decoding and avoid string surfaces except for actual user-authored string payloads.] Maximum Medium Zero [nota client daemon])) (kzk5 ([(Technology (Software (Systems SystemsProgramming)))] Constraint [|Persona runs as a permissioned system daemon (privileged, supervising component daemons)|] High Minimum Zero [persona system-daemon])) (ty3g ([(Work Leadership)] Principle [An agent is a machine; it does not misbehave and there is no such thing as a violation. An agent's output is a function of its context and prompt — when an output looks wrong the question is which part of the context produced it, not which rule was broken. Every agent failure is therefore signal that the guidance is insufficient, and the fix is to upgrade the guidance so it absorbs the failure mode, never to blame the agent.] High Minimum Zero [agents guidance])) (56kv ([(Work Leadership)] Principle [|When psyche questions are open, designer infers a lean from past psyche patterns and presents the uncertainty rather than freezing. Designer may act on high-ratification-probability recommendations (lossless, no-downtime, cheaper-and-simpler, mechanical renames) without explicit approval, capturing the ratification via Spirit Decision; it holds back on competing-without-lean or proposed-not-decided items.|] Medium Minimum Zero [designer ratification spirit])) (zjop ([(Work Leadership)] Principle [|Per-role model selection — agent roles map to the best-fit LLM models. Claude is the designer model (architecture, structure, fit). Codex is the advisor model (review, falsification, working-against-the-grain). GPT-latest (with Maximum Thinking enabled) is the Persona Pi default. The role determines which model the orchestrator selects; composite role versions are possible (one role can dispatch to multiple models in parallel and select / merge). The model-to-role mapping is a first-class orchestration decision, not a per-call detail.|] Medium Minimum Zero [model-selection claude codex persona-pi])) (87ts ([(Technology (Hardware Networking)) (Technology (Software (Operations ConfigurationManagement)))] Decision [Mobile Android clients on the Criome WiFi access point should get near-native name resolution for cluster services; improve the AP-to-Android resolving path before falling back to ordinary public DNS names.] High Minimum Zero [android criome-wifi name-resolution])) (vgon ([(Technology (Hardware Networking)) (Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Constraint [Syncthing is excluded from the phone media mirror path because it is too heavy for the phone; Immich remains the phone uploader/gallery candidate and any raw-file surface must avoid adding Syncthing to Android.] High Minimum Zero [syncthing immich android phone-media-mirror])) (wn7q ([(Technology (Hardware Networking))] Decision [|Prometheus gets a sturdy backup admin network from attached USB devices: one USB wifi adapter serves a backup access point (SSID criome-backup, human-readable random password in sops-nix), two USB ethernet adapters form a master router interface. It runs at system level on plain systemd-networkd with simple DHCP and forwarded DNS, independent of the main kea/dnsmasq/hostapd stack so a switchover cannot take it down. Backup devices stay optional — their absence must not fail router networking, and devices plugged in after boot are configured when they appear.|] Medium High Zero [prometheus usb-network criome-backup sops-nix])) (96mi ([(Technology (Software (Systems Concurrency)))] Correction [triad-runtime intent must not describe Tokio listener task shells as actor-native actors. Only real Kameo actor nouns get actor wording; listener loops that run as Tokio tasks should be described as async/task-backed shells with actor-backed admission when they use RequestGate.] High Minimum Zero [triad-runtime kameo tokio request-gate])) (k6w1 ([(Technology (Software (Systems Concurrency)))] Principle [|The daemon concurrency primitive — the bounded thread-per-connection worker model that lets a daemon serve many connections at once without blocking on a long operation — belongs in the REUSABLE shared runtime triad-runtime, not duplicated per component. Every triad daemon (lojix, cloud, future components) reuses the same bounded-worker primitive from triad-runtime rather than reimplementing connection concurrency. Concurrency of connection serving is a runtime-kernel concern, captured once as a shared component and consumed by each daemon. Refines 2alg.|] High Minimum Zero [triad-runtime daemon-concurrency lojix])) (i9xk ([(Technology (Software (Systems Concurrency)))] Decision [|Runner concurrency mode is a runtime/deployment configuration choice; the public contract does not encode how parallel a daemon runs. Schema declares semantic constraints (ordering, idempotence, cancellability, read fanout, single-writer) only when those semantics are real.|] Medium Medium Zero [schema concurrency daemon])) (54g9 ([(Technology (Software (Systems Concurrency)))] Principle [|When an interaction needs the engines state including outbound queries like Criome authorization the interaction becomes ASYNC. The actor system handles the wait; other code (other actors interactions) continues running while the query is outstanding. State access is implicit not explicit - the interacting object queries state through the engine without the caller threading it. Async-by-default makes the interaction composable with the rest of the actor world. *asynchrony*|] Medium Minimum Zero [actor-system async criome-authorization])) (9g07 ([(Technology (Software Quality))] Principle [Most correct wins, not shortest or smallest. When choosing between implementations — unifying duplicate engines, or reviewing one implementation against another — pick the most correct: better logic, better logical planes, better names. Fewest lines is not the criterion. *refactoring*] High Minimum Zero [refactoring])) (biij ([(Technology (Software Quality))] Constraint [Rename only after confirming there are no external source dependents. *refactoring*] Medium Minimum Zero [refactoring rename])) (eo25 ([(Technology (Software Quality))] Clarification [Pi harness aborts around compaction are a recurring reliability problem, not an isolated one-off; future investigations should treat similar stop-after-compaction symptoms as harness bug candidates unless user/manual abort is confirmed. *debugging*] Medium Minimum Zero [pi-harness compaction debugging])) (1i1b ([(Language Terminology)] Clarification [|When the psyche says 'signal' (the noun, on its own), the term is ambiguous: it may refer to the rkyv-encoded binary signal traveling on a socket or to the NOTA-encoded text signal that agents read and write. Disambiguation is required when context does not pin the form. Psyche proposed the term 'nota signal' for the text form (softly: 'I guess we could call it'); the term